title: Replies to initial written questions raised by Finance Committee Members in examining the Estimates of Expenditure 2012-13
question_text: (a) According to the Administration, the approved estimate for the construction of Trade and Industry Tower in Kai Tak Development Area is $2,645.1 million. Yet the estimated expenditure for 2012-13 is only $158.1 million. What is the timetable for drawing down the remaining provision of $2,477 million or so? How can the works be expedited in order to take forward the developments for energising Kowloon East? (b) Please set out in detail the distribution of resources allocated for the various facilities of the project.
reply_text: (a) The construction of Trade and Industry Tower in Kai Tak Development Area (the Project) commenced in January 2012 and is scheduled for completion in December 2014. The approved project estimate is $2,645.1 million. The revised estimate for 2011-12 is $10 million. The estimate of $158.1 million for 2012-13 is mainly for the foundation and superstructure works. The remaining estimated expenditure of $2,477 million will be incurred in 2013-14 and beyond for the remaining superstructure works, finishing works, and procurement of furniture and equipment. We will closely monitor the project progress and ensure the works are completed on time. (b) The Project is for the construction of a joint-user government office building for accommodating government offices, a community hall and other ancillary facilities. Under the relevant contract, the overall expenditure is broken down by types of works (e.g. piling, building services, building works). As such, breakdown by facilities is not available. Signature: Name in block letters: K K LEUNG Post Title: Director of Architectural Services Date: 27.2.2012 Session 15 FSTB(Tsy) – page
